<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-644] StaleHelper does not close DirectoryStream</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-644</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;StaleHelper&lt;/tt&gt; class introduced in 3.2.0 creates a new &lt;tt&gt;DirectoryStream&lt;/tt&gt; but fails to close it:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/compare/maven-javadoc-plugin-3.1.1..maven-javadoc-plugin-3.2.0#diff-5eee595ccbfac461074d6b07d8983a14R145&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/compare/maven-javadoc-plugin-3.1.1..maven-javadoc-plugin-3.2.0#diff-5eee595ccbfac461074d6b07d8983a14R145&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re using &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/takari/takari-plugin-testing-project&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Takari&apos;s embedded Maven launcher&lt;/a&gt; in our integration tests and this resource leakage causes our tests to fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
